==French==
===Etymology===
Borrowed from the former Provencial ''[[abelha]]'' for "honey bee", from Latin ''[[apicula]]'' meaning "little bee", derived from ''[[apis]]'' for "bee". The indo-european stem is found in the Latin ''[[fucus]]'' for "hornet".

===Pronunciation===
'''abeille'''
*[[IPA]]: /a.bɛj/, [a.bɛːj] (Parisian)
*[[X-SAMPA]]: /a.bEj/, [a.bE:j] (Parisian)

'''une abeille'''
*[[IPA]]: [y.ˈna.bɛːj] (Parisian and Quebec)
*[[X-SAMPA]]: [y."na.bE:j] (Parisian and Quebec)
*{{audio|Fr-Paris-une abeille des abeilles.ogg|Audio (Parisian)}}, {{audio|Fr-abeille-fr_CA.ogg|Audio (Quebec)}}

'''des abeilles'''
*[[IPA]]: [de.ˈza.bɛːj] (Parisian)
*[[X-SAMPA]]: [de."za.bE:j] (Parisian)
*{{audio|Fr-Paris-une abeille des abeilles.ogg|Audio (Parisian)}}

